Present capture data were analyzed together
with transmission data from ORELA, using the R-matrix
code SAMMY. All resonances up to 700 keV were included
in the R matrix. In the fitting procedure,the resonance
energy and the partial widths were allowed to vary
while spin and angular momentum were kept fixed.
Parameters of the resonance at negative energy were
changed with respect to the assumptions in REL-REF of
T.Nakagawa+ to reproduce the thermal-neutron capture
cross section reported in REL-REF of T.A.Walkiewicz+.
Its energy was taken from the level scheme in REL-REF
